phrases: Sorry for getting straight to the point,
but it was 15th in the final rankings this week.
Even my team leader said that if it were not for Niizuma Eiji doing the art,
it would have been canceled a long time ago.
I read the script you faxed in,
and it is kind of dark.
Niizuma also said that he is been finding it boring recently.
Sorry, but I will get him to make up for it with the art somehow.
Well, CROW's final chapter did take away some votes from you.
All right, next time I will be counting on you for a bright, refreshing story more suited to shounen manga!
Man, I cannot believe CROW ended.
I am telling you, those guys are pulling our legs by ending CROW and keeping NATURAL.
This week's NATURAL is so damn boring, too.
I have not even read it yet.
The readers, the editors, and Niizuma, too...
And there is a big gap between Takagi and I.
I do not know what to do anymore.
This restaurant is self-serve, but their tea's really good!
Hiramaru, I am on the phone right now.
What do we think is the best manga in the world?
There is a difference between what manga I think is the best, and what manga is my favorite,
but if I had to pick one, I would say it is Tezuka's Phoenix.
I would have to say The Rose of Versailles and Glass Mask.
I am for SLAM DUNK all the way!
You can really tell a lot about someone by asking them what manga they like.
You would say Ashita no Joe, right?
If you are asking me what my favorite manga is, then yeah.
But I would also give a different answer if you are asking me what I think is the best one.
When I was a kid, I remember reading it here and not being able to sleep that night.
That is the kind of manga you cannot put down until you are done reading it.
When we talk about those, I cannot help but feel that our own manga pales in comparison.
I do not want to make something that is just popular during its own time.
I want to leave behind something that will still be regarded as a masterpiece many years from now.
That is what Eiji is trying to do.
The next one I write will not just be the best manga in Jack...
It will be the best manga ever written!
No, I have not heard anything.
Akina called me a week ago,
I got concerned and called her many times,
but she would not pick up.
Have you tried her editor, Miura?
He said that Akina... would not write anymore.
It seems that even when he visited her apartment, she would not answer her door.
I did not want to trouble you, but I believe you are the one
she opens up to the most.
What do you mean she will not write?
I can drop by Iwase's place, right?
Why do you have to go?
Because I am worried about her, obviously!
Apparently she is been holed up in her apartment for days and will not answer anyone.
She said herself that she would not write anymore, right?
I know how Shuujin feels about this.
Do you know her address and contact info?
But Mashiro, you have never really talked to her before.
Like Eiji said, the rivals we compete with in Jack are also our friends.
There is no changing that fact.
Let us fix up NATURAL with the three of us: you, me and Niizuma!
If you do not answer in the next ten minutes,
I will call the police and get them to break down this door.
But listen to what I have to say.
If you want to quit, then quit.
However, in order to do that you will need to talk to Miura and the Chief Editor
and go through the proper procedures first.
The way you are acting right now is childish.
It is not something the smart Iwase would do.
I do not matter to Ashirogi Mutou.
I do not want you to quit,
but if that is what you have decided, then there is nothing I can do.
Shuujin is grateful that you came into his world and competed with him on his terms.
He was happy to think of you
I am thankful that you are my greatest rival as an author,
and I think of you as one of my comrades who holds the same goals in regards to Jack.
This time, I will be the one to say it.
Let us encourage each other, and do our best!
As Shuujin's rival, you gave him some motivation to keep improving.
that is only what we hoped you would be for us.
It is up to you whether you will keep going or not.
That is all I have to say.
I will drop by again tomorrow.
Show me that you are okay, even if you have to fake it!
I am sorry for not realizing how you felt, even though you called me.
Stop being so stubborn and join Team Fukuda already.
If you do, you will not be alone with your worries anymore.
If you want to quit so badly, I will not stop you.
But I just lost a strong rival in CROW,
so I do not want to lose my greatest rival as an author as well.
I cannot afford to lose to you guys.
I will prove that I can rise to the top again.
All by myself, without joining a team!
I am looking forward to the next NATURAL.
The Chief Editor just got called to the executive room...
Maybe... the Chief is getting replaced?
Well, Hissho Jack is finally getting underway in April.
Speaking of which, the Chief has been so nice lately it is almost creepy.
He is never said anything like that to me before.
A while ago, he called out Do your best! to me, too.
Heishi is the next Chief Editor?!
If Assistant Chief Editor Heishi becomes the new Chief Editor...
In the end, Chief Editor Sasaki and team leader Nakano
were transfered to Hissho Jack based on the strength of their accomplishments.
and Aida is the Assistant Chief.
You are forgetting something important here!
I am a team leader now!
Can you make some time tomorrow?
In light of this news, I would like to pay my respects to all the authors.
I know this is sudden, but at the end of the month, I will be transferring to Hissho Jack.
And also, I am going to become a team leader.
You are in front of the Chief Editor!
Thank you for all you have done for me.
I was happy when you came all the way out to Aomori to see me.
It was me and the Chief back then, too.
Was that really eight years ago?
When you suddenly said If I become the No. 1 author, give me the right to end one manga,
I thought you were just a cheeky little kid.
But now you have gone on to become one of the most prominent authors of Jack.
I am still expecting great things out of you.
I am not really the best yet,
but I am going to make the best manga in the world!
It is just a goal of his.
I am not worried about you at all, Niizuma.
As the chief editor of a new magazine, I will be watching over you.
The Chief Editor is coming all the way out here to see us.
We have been plenty selfish and caused a ton of trouble for him.
Like when I insisted on not going on hiatus when I was in the hospital,
and when we wanted to quit Tanto.
And before that, when we knowingly entered the amateur prize contest,
even though we were experienced authors under contract.
We have to use this opportunity to properly apologize!
He is been here before as the editor of Super Hero Legend.
Because I will no longer be the chief editor of Weekly Shounen Jack,
I can tell you about the favor that Kawaguchi Tarou asked of me when he was still alive.
You did not pass through the serialization committee.
They gave us some feedback, though.
Let us try for the next committee.
I want to become an author who can put out one hit after another as I wait for Taka.
He looks up to me and says he will be a manga artist.
I do not want to let him down.
He is still in elementary school.
He really loves drawing manga, though,
and comes here often to draw.
He is way better than you are.
But he can become a far better manga artist than I could ever be.
So, I want to be active until then.
So that one day you can both be serialized in Jack at the same time?
When he goes professional, take care of him.
When I learned that one of the two middle school students Hattori was meeting at the editing department
It was because of those circumstances
that I often could not keep my cool when it came to you.
We are the ones who have things to apologize for!
No, now that I think about it,
deciding to put TRAP on hold when you were hospitalized until you graduated school was too strict.
The same goes for saying that PCP would be canceled if you could not draw even with Niizuma.
You turned those restrictions right back on me.
No, it is because you gave us those trials that we are who we are now.
We are truly in your debt!
You are who you are now because of your own abilities.
You have done very well to get this far.
I would have probably treated you differently no matter what.
Not in a nice way, though.
If that is true, then I would like to think that you favored us.
Because it was for our own sakes.
But that is all over with.
You are already prolific authors in Jack as Ashirogi Mutou.
And the one you must overcome is Niizuma Eiji.
Niizuma is an amazing manga author,
but if there is anyone who can surpass him,
I think it would be you two.
No, perhaps I am just favoring you again.
No, we will show you that you are not!
I will be expecting that, then.
When I went to visit Niizuma the other day,
he said he was getting his new manga ready.
He said he will be ready to show it to me before I transfer.
Eiji's finally got a new manga.
And it will be ready before the Chief leaves!
I know you said that to the Chief,
but you really have not decided what to do yet, have you?
What are you going to do?
What kind of story is it?
That is not as easy as you make it sound.
No, I actually thought of something after looking at that character you drew.
I have a story that will work!
So, what kind of story did you think up for this character?
The protagonist will receive power from a demon,
and he will look like this while he is using the demon's powers.
So, you will need to make a human version of him for when he is not transformed.
he can force his thoughts onto other people.
It sounds like just your kind of story.
The protagonist is an all-around excellent high school student,
but he is actually a fool for believing that his ideals and way of thinking is correct.
He is convinced that the world will become a better place if more people think like he does.
He is brainwashing people, but he thinks he is doing the right thing.
I cannot say much without seeing it,
but it does not sound very shounen-like to me.
I cannot imagine many people would support that...
A dark hero with a demon's powers?
Because he is a demon, it is probably best to add some black.
This World is Money and Intelligence.
Shuujin, you are going to portray him as a really dark character, right?
Make him think that all evildoers he does not like should be eliminated!
He will look totally evil, then.
If we go too far, Hattori will prune it back for us.
We should not be so cautious!
You have got a storyboard already?!
All that is left is the character design!
Even though he is a zombie, the readers have to like him immediately!
I am going to make a scary horror story.
He already knows without me having to tell him.
This intensity from just a storyboard!
It is so exciting that I am getting goosebumps!
I did not really get it at first when you said zombie, but this is amazing!
Making him fall in love with a human girl is an interesting idea!!
I will make the heroine appealing!
It is a simple story, but there is a human drama here that was not in CROW.
Maybe being No.1 in the world is not just a dream!
The protagonist's ideals are pretty disturbing.
It is not good for it to be that dark, right?
You are the one who told me to do this!
So, what do I do with this?
This World is Money and Intelligence lost to Eiji's standard battle manga in NEXT.
PCP never really made it to the top either.
In the end, it never did beat CROW.
It is because they do not follow the shounen manga archetype.
It is the limitation of an unorthodox style.
What is this all of a sudden?
An unorthodox style suits you, and you are good at dark and disturbing stuff, too.
but there is a limit to how far we can go with just unorthodox.
That is why we will introduce a real mainstream character of justice.
A young man who uses a demon's power for evil,
and a young man who uses a demon's power for good.
By bringing justice into the mix, this will become a standard battle manga.
We can break through the limitations we have had up till now!
So you told me to make it really disturbing because you thought of this?
It will be interesting to show just how evil the black demon can get.
And the white demon will never forgive him for planting his thoughts on others.
It will be a battle of ideals.
A battle of the humans on whom these ideals were implanted.
And a battle of these two protagonists!
And true justice will win in the end!
That is what shounen manga is all about!
The scale is different from anything we have done before!
It is gotten a lot better!
Let us fight against Eiji with this!
So we will end up doing a standard battle manga after all.
It is the end of thinking Ashirogi does unorthodox and Niizuma does standard.
We did not take any detours to get here.
We can draw this because we are who we are now, and no one else could do this.
A standard battle manga that only Ashirogi can do!
Who will win, Ashirogi or Niizuma?
Dreams start when you collide feelings with one another!
As soon as I reach my goals, it all falls through again
We met after such a long time
Has the mood changed for us?
It seemed like more fun back then
Do not stop screaming, do not stop struggling
You have done enough for others
I still, still have something I have not told you yet
Beyond each of my dreams lies yet another dream
Whenever I am close to fulfilling my goals, all effort becomes fruitless
We walk ahead, hold each other, and with little things
we support each other to reach what we promised
When we lack confidence, we put a hand to our heart
and reread the pages we assembled into a story
They lead up to today and continue into the morrow
until the day that our dreams come true
